A LIGHT aircraft crashed near FNB stadium in Nasrec, Joburg, on Sunday, 15 January. Emer-G-Med Spokesman Kyle van Reenen broke the news of the crash on Sunday morning, 15 January, on their social media platforms.“Emer-G-Med paramedics together with multiple emergency service agencies are currently in attendance of a light aircraft crash in the Nasrec area of Johannesburg,” he wrote. “Sadly, two people have lost their lives,” he said. Kyle said the cops and the Civil Aviation Authorities are attending to the matter and will be conducting an investigation looking into the crash.“The South African Police Services are in attendance and will be conducting the necessary investigation together with Civil Aviation Authorities,” he said. In a written statement the South African Civil Aviation Authority (SACAA) said that a preliminary report will be issued out 30 days from the day of this accident.Communications manager, Sisa Majolo said: “The Accident and Incident Investigations Division (AIID) has been informed of an aircraft accident occurrence on Sun, 15 January 2023 at 0900 local time.  The accident occurred at Nasrec next to FNB stadium, south of Johannesburg in the Gauteng Province. "The aircraft departed from Grand Central Airport in the Gauteng province on a training flight with the intention to land back at the same Airport. Onboard the aircraft were two occupants, who both sustained fatal injuries. The aircraft itself sustained substantial damage.The Accident was reported by the Aeronautical Rescue Coordination Centre (ARCC)," he said. 